(121, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'ARA', 102, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'ELEMENTARY ARABIC II', 'A continuation of Arabic 101 from the  semester. Introduction of writing complex sentences and reading paragraphs. In addition, more vocabulary building, and longer conversational sessions. This course will require basic fundamentals of the Arabic language such as reading simple sentences and engaging in a simple conversation. This course is designed to help students gain more knowledge in their vocabularies, grammar, and oral skills.', 4.0, '', '', 'ARA 101', ''),
(122, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'ARA', 104, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'INTERMEDIATE ARABIC II', 'A continuation of Arabic 103. This course is designed to enable students to engage in an intermediate conversation with a native Arabic speaker in different scenarios. The course will cover all the materials which can help a student with writing and reading as a professional Arabic speaker.', 4.0, '', '', '', ''),
