(125, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'ASL', 101, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'BEGINNING AMERICAN SIGN LANGUAGE I', 'An introductory course in American Sign Language as developed and used by the Deaf community in most areas of North America. Everyday communication is the centerpiece of every lesson. Topics revolve around sharing information about our environment and us. Grammar is introduced in context, with an emphasis on developing question and answer skills. You learn conversational strategies to help you maintain a conversation. Students will also be exposed to native signers modeling appropriate language and cultural behaviors in various situations. Interaction activities allow you to rehearse what you_??ve learned. \n\n', 4.0, '', '', '', ''),
