(309, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'BME', 442, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'Microbiomechanics', 'This course covers the application of mechanical principles to biotechnology and to understanding life at its smallest scales. Topics will vary with each course offering. Sample topics include force generation by protein polymerization, the mechanisms of bacterial motion, and the separation of biological molecules in porous media.', 2.0, '', '', 'permission of instructor', 'BME 442 (P), MSC 442, TEB 442'),
