(336, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CAS', 85, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'English as a Second Language (ESL) Course for Arts, Sciences and', 'This advanced-level course aims to address two specific weak points of graduate-level and adult English as a Second Language learners: writing style and real-life conversational skills. The writing component of this course will focus on implementable, concrete strategies for improving academic and professional writing; writing assignments relevant to the students'' actual current professional development will be assigned. The conversational component of this course will focus on helping students develop fluency and confidence dealing with typical spoken exchanges in workplace and social settings.', 0.0, '', '', '', ''),
