(576, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 161, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'SOCIAL PSYCHOLOGY AND INDIVIDUAL DIFFERENCES', 'Introduction to field of social psychology and overview of research on individual differences in personality. Topics include: the self, attributions, social cognition, interpersonal attraction, relationships, helping, social influence, traits, and motive dispositions. Students complete and receive personal feedback on a number of personality measures.\n', 4.0, '', 'S1CSP003, S1CSP005, S1CSP006, S1CSP008', '', 'CSP 161 (P), PSY 161'),
(577, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 161, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'SOCIAL PSYCHOLOGY AND INDIVIDUAL DIFFERENCES', 'Fulfills upper-level writing requirement.', 0.5, '', 'S1CSP006', '[A] Instructor''s permission required', 'CSP 161W (P), PSY 161W'),
(578, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 209, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'PSYCHOLOGY OF HUMAN SEXUALITY', 'Survey course on understanding sexuality. Includes such topics as biological sexual differentiation, gender role, gender-linked social behaviors, reproduction issues, intimacy, and the role of social and personal factors in psychosexual development.', 4.0, '', 'S1CSP006', 'PSY 101', 'CSP 209 (P), PSY 209, WST 209'),
(579, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 209, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'PSYCHOLOGY OF HUMAN SEXUALITY', '', 0.5, '', '', '[A] Instructor''s permission required', 'CSP 209W (P), PSY 209W'),
(580, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 211, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'INTRODUCTION TO STATISTICAL METHODS IN PSYCHOLOGY', 'Introduction to the use of statistics in psychological research.  Topics include descriptive statistics, correlation and regression, and inferential statistics.  Examples are drawn from social and personality psychology.  Logic of statistical inference and proper interpretation of research findings are emphasized. ( & )  Please note that, because of the significant overlap between them, students may earn degree credit for only one of these courses:  CSP/PSY 211, STT 211 and STT 212.', 4.0, '', '  ', '', 'CSP 211 (P), PSY 211'),
(581, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 219, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'RESEARCH METHODS IN PSYCHOLOGY', 'An introduction to the basic concepts, logic, and procedures needed to do psychological research.  Hands-on experience with all major phases of the research process is provided, including:  surveying the existing literature, developing research hypotheses, collecting and analyzing data, and reporting the results in manuscript form', 4.0, '', ' ', 'PSY 101\n	\n\nPSY 101 Required\n\nPSY 211 Required\n	\n\n', 'CSP 219W (P), PSY 219W'),
(582, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 232, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'PSYCHOLOGY OF CONSUMERISM', '', 4.0, '', '', 'Examines the psychology behind product placement, marketing of products, brand identity and advertising to consumers.', 'CSP 232 (P), PSY 232'),
(583, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 232, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'PSYCHOLOGY OF CONSUMERISM', '', 0.5, '', '', '[A] Instructor''s permission required', 'CSP 232W (P), PSY 232W'),
(584, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 262, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'AN APPROACH TO HUMAN MOTIVATION', 'This course provides a review of the theoretical and empirical development of a contemporary approach to human motivation, namely, Self-Determination Theory, which originated at the University of Rochester and is currently researched by scholars around the world.  Topics will also include applications of Self-Determination Theory to such domains as psychopathology and psychological health, work, education, sport, and culture', 4.0, '', 'S1CSP003, S1CSP004, S1CSP005, S1CSP006, S1CSP008', 'CSP/PSY 161 OR 181', 'CSP 262 (P), PSY 262'),
(585, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 262, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'AN APPROACH TO HUMAN MOTIVATION', 'Fulfills upper-level writing requirement.', 0.5, '', '', '[A] Instructor''s permission required', 'CSP 262W (P), PSY 262W'),
(586, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 276, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'PSYCHOLOGY OF PARENTING', 'Parenting and family life are emphasized from developmental, ecological, and cross-cultural perspectives. Caregiving in diverse family forms and cultures is studied in relation to adult-child interactions, parent/school/community relations, family roles, laws, and parenting skills. Issues related to aspects of diversity in contemporary families are included.', 4.0, '', 'S1CSP004, S1CSP006, S1CSP009', 'PSY 171', 'CSP 276 (P), PSY 276'),
(587, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 278, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'ADOLESCENT DEVELOPMENT', 'This course surveys theory and research relating to normal development during adolescence.  Adolescent development is examined in a variety of contexts, including families, peer groups, and schools, and issues pertaining to biological, social, and cognitive development are discussed.', 4.0, '', 'S1CSP006, S1CSP009', '', 'CSP 278 (P), PSY 278'),
(588, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 278, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'ADOLESCENT DEVELOPMENT', 'Fulfills upper-level writing requirement.', 0.5, '', '', '[A] Instructor''s permission required', 'CSP 278W (P), PSY 278W'),
(589, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 282, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'ABNORMAL PSYCHOLOGY', 'This course provides a conceptual overview to the field of psychopathology.  We will discuss assessment and diagnosis, etiology, developmental course, treatment, and prognosis of the major psychological disorders.  Current theory and research will be emphasized.', 4.0, '', 'S1CSP001, S1CSP006, S1CSP007', '', 'CSP 282 (P), PSY 282'),
(590, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 282, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'ABNORMAL PSYCHOLOGY', '', 0.5, '', '', 'Fulfills upper-level writing requirement.', 'CSP 282W (P), PSY 282W'),
(591, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 283, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'BEHAVIORAL MEDICINE', 'An overview of the application of behavior/lifestyle change approaches to the treatment of medical disorders, and the examination of interfaces between behavior and physiology. Topics include diabetes, cardiovascular risk factors, chronic pain, and cancer.', 4.0, '', 'S1CSP001, S1CSP006, S1HLS002, S1PH004', 'PSY 101 Required', 'CSP 283 (P), PSY 283'),
(592, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 283, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'BEHAVIORAL MEDICINE', 'Fulfills upper-level writing requirement.', 0.5, '', '', '[A] Instructor''s permission required', 'CSP 283W (P), PSY 283W');
