(595, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 356, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'RESEARCH IN ADOLESCENT DEVELOPMENT', 'This course provides guided, direct experiences with research on adolescent development, with a particular focus on adolescence in the contest of family relationships.', 4.0, '', '', '[A] Instructor''s permission required', 'CSP 356 (P), PSY 356'),
