(616, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 519, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'DATA ANALYSIS:GEN LIN APP 11', '', 3.0, '', '', '[A] Instructor''s permission required', ''),
(617, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSP', 525, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'SECONDARY DATA ANALYSIS', 'Secondary data analysis refers to empirical research that uses data collected by someone else for \nanother primary purpose. This methodology is well-established across disciplines and offers the potential to conduct high-impact research using considerably less time and resources than is usually required with primary data collection. The goal of this course is to equip junior scholars with the ability to incorporate secondary data into their program of research. Although the same basic research principles apply to all data analysis (whether primary or secondary), the experience of using secondary data is unique in some ways. This course will review skills, techniques, and issues that are necessary for accurate and high-quality use of secondary data. Using an applied approach, students will acquire knowledge of secondary data analysis through completing each step of their own empirical project. ', 3.0, '', '', '[A] Instructor''s permission required', ''),
