(673, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'EAS', 141, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'BASIC MECHANICAL FABRICATION', 'This course will teach students the safe and effective use of basic machine tools such as lathes, mills, band-saws and drill presses. Students will complete a number of projects that utilize these principles. Grades will be based on the successful completion of these projects. A course paper will be a written documentation of the procedures necessary to complete one of the projects done during the class. The paper will be graded on content, organization and clarity.', 2.0, '', '', 'Instructor Permission required, [K] Open only to freshmen and sophomores', ''),
(674, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'EAS', 141, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'BASIC MECHANICAL FABRICATION', 'This course will teach students the safe and effective use of basic machine tools such as lathes, mills, band-saws and drill presses. Students will complete a number of projects that utilize these principles. Grades will be based on the successful completion of these projects. A course paper will be a written documentation of the procedures necessary to complete one of the projects done during the class. The paper will be graded on content, organization and clarity.', 2.0, '', '', 'Instructor Permission required, [K] Open only to freshmen and sophomores', ''),
