(743, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'ECO', 207, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'INTERMEDIATE MICROECONOMICS-HONORS', 'This course shows how the choices of consumers and firms interact through markets to determine all the factors related to economic well being. In comparison to other sections of ECO 207, this section develops these choices more formally and mathematically. ', 4.0, '', 'S1ECO001, S1ECO003, S1ECO004, S1ECO006', 'Strong performance in ECO 108, completion of MTH 161, MTH 171, or completion of MTH 141 and 142', ''),
(744, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'ECO', 208, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'TOPICS IN MICROECONOMIC THEORY', 'This course is a sequel to ECO 207. It covers a variety of topics in microeconomics. The precise content varies, but usually includes a more detailed look at alternative normative criteria, applied game theory, auction theory, the problem of social cost, and a little voting theory.', 4.0, '', '', 'ECO 207 and Calculus, [A] Instructor''s permission required', ''),
