(891, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'ENG', 464, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'FILMS OF THE 1930S', 'We will screen a selection of films from the richest period in Hollywood cinema, paying particular attention to such mattes as the establishment of genres, the advances in film technology, and the important connections between the films and their times, especially in the context of the Great Depression.  Titles will include "Public Enemy," "Bride of Frankenstein," "42nd Street," "The Wizard of Oz," among others.', 4.0, '', 'H1ENG010, H1ENG016', '[E] Not open to freshman', 'AH 264, AH 464, ENG 264 (P), ENG 464, FMS 261'),
