(897, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'ENG', 475, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'SEMINAR IN WRITING: FICTION', 'This is a workshop for students who have completed ENG 275, or have extensive experience writing fiction on their own, and are ready to concentrate on more ambitious projects. We''ll read short stories by contemporary writers along with fiction by the students in the workshop, and we''ll discuss ways writers can sharpen the conversation between text and reader. We''ll also consider editing and reviewing techniques. Students will be expected to write and revise at least three original stories or three sections of a longer work of fiction. Permission of instructor required.', 4.0, '', 'H1ENG009, H1ENG015', '[A] Instructor''s permission required', 'ENG 375 (P), ENG 475'),
