(1006, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'HIS', 501, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'Worlds of Inquiry', 'History 501 _??Worlds of Inquiry_ѝ introduces students to the interests of the Rochester faculty, which  into three spheres of inquiry -- the world of nations, which emphasizes the complications of government, nationalism, war, and power; the world of goods, which concentrates on commerce and trade, the supporting institutions and the consequence of various modes of production and consumption; and the world of knowledge, which addresses how humans have known the world, how that knowledge has changed, and the purposes and uses humans have made of knowledge. Students will read a sequence of exemplary works in each world _?? works that will acquaint them with the rudiments of each sphere, the problems under investigation and some of the solutions offered.', 5.0, '', '', '[Q] Open only to graduate students in offering department', ''),
