(1360, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'OPT', 223, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'QUANTUM THEORY', 'Intro to quantum mechanics in the context of modern optics and optical technology. Wave mechanics as applied to electrons in crystals and in quantum wells and the optical properties of materials. Semiconductor junctions in photodetectors and photoemitters.', 4.0, '', '', 'PHY 123 or 143, MTH 281 may be taken concurrently', ''),
(1361, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'OPT', 225, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'SOURCES AND DETECTORS', 'This course provides the basic concepts required for understanding radiometry and the operation of optical sources and photodetectors. It covers important sources such as lasers and light-emitting diodes as well several types of photodetectors. Students should also register for the complementary lab, Optics 204', 4.0, '', '', '', ''),
(1362, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'OPT', 232, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'OPTO-MECHANICAL', 'The mechanical design and analysis of optical components and systems will be studied. Topics will include kinematic mounting of optical elements, the analysis of adhesive bonds, and the influence of environmental effects such as gravity, temperature, and vibration on the performance of optical systems. Additional topics include analysis of adaptive optics, the design of lightweight mirrors, thermo-optic and stress-optic (stress birefringence) effects. Emphasis will be placed on integrated analysis which includes the data transfer between optical design codes and mechanical FEA codes. A term project is required for ME 432.', 4.0, '', '', '', 'ME 232 (P), ME 432, MSC 432, OPT 232, OPT 432, TEO 432, TME 432'),
(1363, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'OPT', 244, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'LENS DESIGN', '', 4.0, '', '', '', ''),
(1364, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'OPT', 247, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'ADVANCED THIN FILM COATINGS', 'Specialty and custom coatings and their scientific applications and business uses.', 4.0, '', '', 'OPT 246', 'OPT 247 (P), OPT 447, TEO 447'),
(1365, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'OPT', 248, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'VISION AND THE EYE', 'How the human eye''s optical and neural factors process color and spatial information includes comparison with the design and capabilities of other animals'' eyes.', 4.0, '', '', '', 'BCS 223, OPT 248 (P), OPT 448, TEO 448'),
(1366, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'OPT', 261, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'INTERFERENCE AND DIFFRACTION', 'Complex representation of waves; scalar diffraction theory; Fresnel and Fraunhofer diffraction and application to measurement; diffraction and image formation; optical transfer function; coherent optical systems, optical data processing, and holography. ', 4.0, '', '', 'MTH 164, PHY 122 or 142', 'OPT 261 (P), PHY 261'),
(1367, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'OPT', 287, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'MATHEMATICAL METHODS FOR OPTICS & PHYSICS', 'Techniques used in mathematical study of optical phenomena. Emphasis on gaining insight and experience in the use of these powerful and elegant tools for describing, solving and resolving optical systems and schema.', 4.0, '', '', 'MTH 164, MTH 281', 'MTH 287, OPT 287 (P)'),
(1368, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'OPT', 307, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'SEM PRACTICUM', 'Overview of techniques for using the SEM (Scanning Electron Microscope) and Scanning Probe (AFM, STM) and analyzing data. Students perform independent lab projects by semester''s end.', 4.0, '', '', '[O] Departmental permission required', 'MSC 307, MSC 507, OPT 307 (P), OPT 407'),
(1369, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'OPT', 311, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'OPTICS SENIOR DESIGN PROJECT', 'Documenting each stage,student teams design, build, and test an optical device or instrument for a faculty, community or industrial sponsor.', 4.0, '', '', 'Open only to Optics seniors.', ''),
