(1502, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'PHY', 597, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'RESEARCH SEMINAR', 'A () - Noncredit course given once per week, required of all first-year graduate students. The seminar consists of lectures and discussions on various aspects of being an effective teaching assistant, including interactions with undergraduate student body and cross-cultural issues.\nB () - Noncredit course given once per week required of all first-year graduate students. Members of the faculty discuss topics in their curent area of research interest.', 0.0, '', '', '', ''),
(1503, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'PHY', 599, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'PEDAGOGY & GROUP LEADERSHIP', 'This course is designed as a follow-up course for an experienced Workshop Leader, titled a lead Workshop Leader Teaching Assistant (TA). Typically, the TA attends the weekly Workshop Leader Training meeting that offers specialized support and training to develop leadership skills, to foster ongoing communication among faculty members and study group leaders, and to provide an environment for review of study group related issues. Students spend the semester teaching three to four workshops during the  semester introductory physics courses. ', 0.0, '', '', '', ''),
