(1839, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'WST', 396, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'WOMEN''S STUDIES SEMINAR', 'Juniors and seniors only or prerequisite course in African American Literature, American Literature or Women''s Studies. Interested students should contact the Women''s Studies Department.', 4.0, '', '', '[G] Special application required [J] Permission of School Dean required', ''),
(1840, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'WST', 397, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'HONORS-INDEPENDENT THESIS', 'Open only to senior majors or by permission of instructor. Honors in Research recognizes the completion of a distinguished thesis, research paper of approximately 35 pages researched and written under the direction of the faculty advisor, and approved by the faculty advisor and second reader. It is expected that this thesis will be based on research undertaken through WST 393H and WST 394H, and completed in WST 397.', 4.0, '', '', '[G] Special application required [J] Permission of School Dean required', ''),
