(1894, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CSC', 285, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'ALGORITHMS & ELECTIONS', 'The focus of this course is on using algorithms to manipulate elections and on using complexity to protect elections from such manipulative attacks.  Among the attacks we will study are manipulation, bribery and control. Students taking this course at the 400 level may be required to complete additional tests, readings, or assignments.', 4.0, '', '', 'Prerequisites: At least one of the following:  MTH 150, MTH 143, MTH162, MTH172, PSC107, CSC280, CSC 281, CSC 282.', 'CSC 285 (P), CSC 485, TCS 485'),
