(1911, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'PHL', 252, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'PHILOSOPHY OF SCIENCE', 'This is a contemporary introduction to the philosophy of science. We will discuss what science is and how it works with an eye towards determining what role it should play in our understanding of the world.  Some questions we will address include: Are our best scientific theories literally true? Do quarks (and other things we can_??t see) really exist? What is a law of nature?  Is there really a scientific method?  Does science provide the best way to think about the world, or are there other, equally good, ways?  ', 4.0, '', 'H1PHL003, N1CHM006', '', 'PHL 252 (P), PHL 252W, PHL 452'),
