(1914, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'PHL', 267, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'BRITISH EMPIRICISM', 'This is a mixed lecture/discussion course on the history of British empiricism.  We will read Locke, Berkeley, Hume and Newton on epistemology, scientific method, perception and the relationship between God and nature.', 4.0, '', 'Several papers, presentations, reading quizzes.', 'PHL 202.', 'PHL 267 (P), PHL 467'),
