(2084, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'CLT', 101, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'MEXICO, DF: GLOBAL METROPOLIS', 'Called by some _??the capital of the 21st century,_ѝ Greater Mexico City is inhabited by close to 20 million people. The Distrito Federal (DF) and capital of Mexico is today the largest metroopolitan area in the western hemisphere and third largest city in the world by population. Established by the Spanish in 1524 on the ruins of the Aztec city TenochtitlՍn they had destroyed, Mexico City is a global center of finance, culture, and industry. This course examines the development of this vibrant megalopolis over the 20th and 21st centuries using literature, film, politics, tourism, music and the arts, cultural geography, architectural space, and essays by urban wanderers to try and get a handle on a space that seems to contradict itself at every turn.', 4.0, '', '', '', 'CLT 101D (P), SP 277, SP 477'),
