(2100, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'SP', 205, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'SPAIN: PAST, PRESENT AND FUTURE', 'This course explores selected topics from the early cultural life of the Iberian Peninsula to the burning issues of the 21st century. Topics vary from semester to semester but focus on changing notions of what it means to be _??Spanish;_ѝ questions of cultural, religious, and ethnic inclusion and exclusion; the rise and  of empire; Spain in America; war, peace, and reconciliation; terror at home; and Spain in the new Europe. Students will critique the myths, stereotypes, and realities of Spanish cultural identities as they examine representative examples of art, architecture, photography, music, sports, culinary arts, television, and film. Taught in Spanish.', 4.0, '', 'H1INT006, H1MLC001', 'SP 200', 'SP 205 (P), SP 405'),
