(2125, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'GER', 218, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'DEEP THOUGHTS WITH GERMAN THINKERS', 'Why are we here? Why do we think what we think? Why do we like art? Appreciate music? Why do we create? Contemplate? Heal? Destroy? All of these big questions had answers_?_once upon a time. And most of those answers were in_?_German! That_??s right: from the late 18th century to the middle of the 20th century German thinkers dominated the intellectual landscape of the world. This course will look at small texts by some of the most important German writers, musicians and philosophers during this period: Goethe, Kant, Beethoven, Hegel, Marx, Nietzsche, Freud, Schoenberg, Benjamin, Heidegger, Adorno and more. Additionally we will look at scientific and medical writings during this period to better understand why before 1933 Germans won more Nobel prizes than Britain and America combined. This course will be taught in English and all the literature will be in English.', 4.0, '', '', '', 'CLT 223, CLT 423, ENG 240, GER 218 (P), GER 418, HIS 298'),
