(2129, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'ENG', 508, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'TEXT AND IMAGE, MANUSCRIPT TO PRINT', 'We will study defining characteristics of an array of artifacts from manuscript and print cultures, assessing the continuities and disconnects that mark these media across the conventional divide of Middle Ages and Renaissance and beyond. We will focus on a high literary writer (Chaucer), a monument of popular culture (Robin Hood), and a broad genre (exoticism in MSS of Alexander the Great and *Mandeville_??s Travels*). In all three cases we will examine the relations of text and image, and attend to what these tell us about the material artifact, cultural registers, reception histories, diverse audiences, the circulation and afterlife of texts. Students will be asked to make transcriptions, to examine actual artifacts in Rare Books and Special Collections, to compare digital copies of MSS and printed editions, to apply techniques of analytic and descriptive bibliography, to produce edited versions of the texts examined, and to shape their analyses through recent arguments about the history of the book.', 5.0, '', '', '', ''),
(2130, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'JPN', 407, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'FILM AS OBJECT', 'The tangible object at the origin of the onscreen image: the social, cultural and historical value of motion pictures and national film cinemas through an understanding of "Film" as an organic object.', 4.0, '', 'H1JPN010', '', 'CLT 230, CLT 430, ENG 258, ENG 458, FMS 243, FMS 443, JPN 207 (P), JPN 407'),
