(2164, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'FR', 241, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'LE NOUVEAU ROMAN', 'This course will focus on the experimental style of the French novel, labelled as the nouveau roman in the 1950s and 1960s. We will examine the literary tendencies that attempted to define anew the purpose of the novel, and will discuss novels and theoretical work by writers such as Marguerite Duras, Alain Robbe-Grillet, Nathalie Sarraute, Michel Butor, as well as early work by Patrick Modiano, the 2014 Nobel Prize recipient in Literature. The literary style of the nouveau roman emerged in dialogue with the film movement known as the French New Wave, and a number of films, such as Alain Resnais_?? "Hiroshima, Mon amour" (1958) and "Last Year in Marienbad" (1961) will be included in class discussion and analysis. All readings and class discussions will be in French.', 4.0, '', '', '', 'FR 241 (P), FR 441'),
(2165, 'Arts, Sciences, and Engineering', 'FR', 441, 'MAIN_COURSE', 'LE NOUVEAU ROMAN', 'This course will focus on the experimental style of the French novel, labelled as the nouveau roman in the 1950s and 1960s. We will examine the literary tendencies that attempted to define anew the purpose of the novel, and will discuss novels and theoretical work by writers such as Marguerite Duras, Alain Robbe-Grillet, Nathalie Sarraute, Michel Butor, as well as early work by Patrick Modiano, the 2014 Nobel Prize recipient in Literature. The literary style of the nouveau roman emerged in dialogue with the film movement known as the French New Wave, and a number of films, such as Alain Resnais_?? "Hiroshima, Mon amour" (1958) and "Last Year in Marienbad" (1961) will be included in class discussion and analysis. All readings and class discussions will be in French.', 4.0, '', '', '', 'FR 241 (P), FR 441'),
